The commit message is especially vague about why the Android API is insufficient to accomplish the goals of these apps, as well as justification that the additions are needed and safe. Until this is provided, I'm -1.

Patch Set 2:

> The commit message is especially vague about why the Android API is
 > insufficient to accomplish the goals of these apps, as well as
 > justification that the additions are needed and safe. Until this is
 > provided, I'm -1.

There is no Android API. The CMSDK API does provide the same control, however, apps can't use it because connecting to the ProfileManagerService is prohibited through SELinux. I figured this was intentional - if it is a bug and that bug is fixed, regular apps could implement the same Locale plugin functionality (or Tasker et al could integrate the functionality). If you can confirm this is a bug I'm happy to abandon this PR. If you can confirm this is intentional, I'll place that explanation in the commit message.

Re security: switched profile notifications are broadcasted publicly anyway, so no access control needed. Switching profiles does not control more features than allowed through WRITE_SETTINGS, so I believe that should be a sufficient restriction - but I'm no CM/Lineage dev, so there might be room for improvements.

Patch Set 2: -Code-Review

I'll leave this for the more app oriented developers then, but please update your commit message.
Patch Set 3: Commit message was updated.

Patch Set 3:

While we are on this let report a nasty bug in Profiles which wasn't present in CM13. Maybe is related to this commit hre.
To reproduce: Set Lock screen disabled in the active profile and reboot. You end up with black screen, no launcher, only SystemUI is running, you can only expand status bar and that's pretty much all you can do. Seems like security issue blocking launcher even built-in Trebuchet. The only way to get out of this is to delete /data/system/profiles.xml and reboot. And you loose a bunch of your settings on top of everything.
BTW this profiles feature is the only way I know of using fingerprint without lock screen on your way.

 > you can do. Seems like security issue blocking launcher even
 > built-in Trebuchet. The only way to get out of this is to delete
 > /data/system/profiles.xml and reboot. And you loose a bunch of your
 > settings on top of everything.
 > BTW this profiles feature is the only way I know of using
 > fingerprint without lock screen on your way.

In an effort to spare anyone else the pain of re/setting/s.
